==English==
===Noun===
'''brahmin'''
# Scholar, teacher, priest, intellectual, researcher, scientist, knowledge-seeker or knowledge-worker.
# A member of the [[Hindu]] priestly [[caste]], responsible for spread of knowledge & spirituality. 
# One who has realized or attemps to realize 'Brahman' i.e. God or supreme knowledge.
# Social and cultural elite. 
# A learned person of refined taste and mild manners.

===Adjective===
'''brahmin'''
# Of or relating to the [[caste]] of Brahmins.
# Scholarly

